<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d320fn1">Sent to the United States Naval
                                Attaché London, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-21">December 21, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>From the President for the <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former
                                Naval Person</gloss> personal and secret No. 242.</p>
                        <p>Following is the substance of letter<note n="2" xml:id="d320fn2">The
                                reference is to Roosevelt’s letter of December 11, 1942, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_498">p.
                                498</ref>.</note> which courier has for you: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“In spite of Stalin’s inability to meet with us I think we should
                                    plan a meeting at once with our respective military staffs. I
                                    should like to meet in Africa about January 15th. There is I
                                    believe a satisfactory and safe place just north of Casablanca.
                                    It might be wise for some of our military men to precede us by a
                                    few days to clear the ground. I should think if we could have
                                    four or five days together we could clear up all of our
                                    business.</p>
                                <p>“Will you let me know what you think of this.”</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>